    "title": "I'm gonna need you to stand back.",
    "description": "Fires 9 E-tech orbs: 1 central shot and 8 in a ring that contracts and expands in flight. On hit, each orb deals impact damage and triggers an equal elemental splash explosion treated as grenade damage. The thrown reload still explodes on contact or after a short delay."
  },
  "notes": "Its low fire rate makes fire-rate bonuses especially valuable. The thrown reload blast is dangerous enough to down the user, and it cannot roll a vertical grip or the Gentle prefix. Firing straight up distorts the ring pattern, though it still contracts and expands. Each pellet adds a full elemental splash instance that cannot crit, while the impact hit can, and grenade damage bonuses increase the splash. Non-elemental versions can spawn as well, with purple pellets that deal non-elemental impact and explosive splash.",
